---
/**
 * Recover page — for a customer who has lost their account number.
 *
 * No email or personal data is stored on the Lattice side, so recovery
 * goes through Stripe, which holds the customer's email for billing. The
 * account number is written into every Stripe payment receipt (see the
 * invoice footer set in server/api/internal/stripe/webhook.go) and into
 * the Stripe customer metadata. See docs/BILLING_INTEGRATION.md §6.
 */
import Layout from '@/layouts/Layout.astro';

// Stripe-hosted customer billing portal login URL. Get this from the
// Stripe Dashboard → Settings → Billing → Customer portal, after enabling
// the portal (Phase 1, step 4). REPLACE before launch.
const BILLING_PORTAL_URL = 'https://billing.stripe.com/p/login/REPLACE_ME';
---
<Layout
  title="Recover your account number"
  description="Lost your Lattice VPN account number? Here's how to get it back."
>
  <div class="pt-32 pb-20 mx-auto max-w-2xl px-6">
    <div class="text-center mb-10">
      <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full holo-glass px-4 py-1.5 text-xs font-mono text-mint-400 mb-6">
        RECOVER ACCESS
      </span>
      <h1 class="font-display font-bold text-4xl md:text-5xl text-white mb-4">
        Lost your account number?
      </h1>
      <p class="text-slate-300">
        Lattice keeps no email, password, or personal account — so we
        can't email it to you directly. But it's recorded in two places
        you control through Stripe.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Option 1: receipts -->
    <div class="holo-glass rounded-2xl p-7 mb-5">
      <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-lg text-white mb-2">
        1. Check your payment receipt
      </h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-slate-300">
        Every receipt Stripe emails you for Lattice VPN prints your account
        number in its footer. Search your inbox for
        <span class="font-mono text-mint-400">Lattice VPN account number</span>
        — it will be on the most recent receipt.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Option 2: billing portal -->
    <div class="holo-glass rounded-2xl p-7 mb-5">
      <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-lg text-white mb-2">
        2. Open your billing portal
      </h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-slate-300 mb-4">
        The Stripe billing portal lets you confirm or manage your
        subscription. You sign in with the email you paid with — Stripe
        emails you a secure login link, so only you can get in.
      </p>
      <a
        href={BILLING_PORTAL_URL}
        class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 rounded-full holo-glass-strong text-white font-medium text-sm px-6 py-3 hover:border-mint-500/40 transition-all"
      >
        Open billing portal
        <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"><path d="M7 17L17 7M7 7h10v10"/></svg>
      </a>
    </div>

    <!-- Reassurance + support -->
    <div class="rounded-xl border border-mint-500/20 bg-mint-500/5 px-5 py-4 mb-6">
      <p class="text-sm text-slate-300">
        Good to know: while your subscription is active, devices you've
        already connected keep working. You only need the account number
        to set up a <em>new</em> device.
      </p>
    </div>

    <p class="text-center text-xs text-slate-500 font-mono">
      Still can't find it? Email
      <a href="mailto:support@latticevpn.ai" class="text-mint-400 underline">support@latticevpn.ai</a>.
    </p>
  </div>
</Layout>
